    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>END YOKE PINCH BOLTS</title>
            <para>For the proper pinch bolt inspection maintenance intervals refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the
                CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
            <para>Visually inspect that the plastic collar has been sheared off. If the plastic collar and other portion
                of the hex nut are present, torque the nut until they shear off. If the nut appears loose, do not
                tighten it further. Install a new nut.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
